----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dashboard Design
Page 1: Sales Overview - Executive Summary
KPIs: Total Sales, Profit, Profit Margin %, Order Count

Charts:
Sales & Profit Trend (Line chart by Month)
Sales by Region (Map or Bar Chart)
Top 5 Products by Revenue (Bar Chart)
Sales by Channel (Pie/Donut Chart)

Page 2: Product Performance
Table or Matrix:
Product Category, Subcategory, Total Sales, Profit, Margin
Visuals:
Clustered bar: â€œSales by Product Categoryâ€
Scatter: â€œProfit vs Sales by Productâ€

Page 3: Regional Analysis
Map: Sales by Country/City
Column chart: Sales by Region and Year
KPI Card: Top-performing region

Page 4: Customer Insights
Table: Top 10 Customers by Revenue
Funnel: Sales pipeline by stage (if available)
KPI: Repeat Customers (%)

| Metric           | Formula (DAX)                           | Description              |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Total Sales      | `SUM(Sales[SalesAmount])`               | Total revenue            |
| Total Cost       | `SUM(Sales[TotalProductCost])`          | Total cost of goods sold |
| Total Profit     | `[Total Sales] - [Total Cost]`          | Profit                   |
| Profit Margin %  | `DIVIDE([Total Profit], [Total Sales])` | Profit percentage        |
| Order Count      | `COUNTROWS(Sales)`                      | Number of orders         |
| Avg. Order Value | `DIVIDE([Total Sales], [Order Count])`  | Average order revenue    |



